'''''Thermodesulfobacterium commune''''' is a species of [[Sulfate-reducing bacteria]]. It is small, [[Gram-negative]], straight rod-shaped, obligately anaerobic and has an optimum growth temperature of {{convert|70|°C|°F}}. Its type strain is YSRA-1.<ref name="ZeikusDawson1983">{{cite journal|last1=Zeikus|first1=J. G.|last2=Dawson|first2=M. A.|last3=Thompson|first3=T. E.|last4=Ingvorsen|first4=K.|last5=Hatchikian|first5=E. C.|title=Microbial Ecology of Volcanic Sulphidogenesis: Isolation and Characterization of Thermodesulfobacterium commune gen. nov. and sp. nov.,|journal=Microbiology|volume=129|issue=4|year=1983|pages=1159–1169|issn=1350-0872|doi=10.1099/00221287-129-4-1159}}</ref>

