{{Taxobox | image = | image_caption = | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Planctomycetes]] | classis = [[Planctomycetacia]] | subclassis = | ordo = [[Planctomycetales]] | subordo = | familia = [[Planctomycetaceae]] | genus = ''[[Thermogutta]]'' | species = '''''T. terrifontis''''' | binomial = '''''Thermogutta terrifontis''''' | binomial_authority = Slobodkina et al. 2015<ref name=Thermogutta-terrifontis>{{cite journal |last1=Parte |first1=A.C. |title=Thermogutta |journal=www.bacterio.net |url=http://www.bacterio.net/thermogutta.html}}</ref> | type_strain = DSM 26237, VKM B-2805, strain R1<ref name=UniProt>{{cite journal |title=Thermogutta terrifontis |journal=www.uniprot.org |url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/1331910 |language=en}}</ref> | subdivision = | synonyms = }}
'''''Thermogutta terrifontis''''' is a [[thermophilic]] bacterium from the genus of ''[[Thermogutta]]'' which has been isolated from a [[hot spring]] from [[Kurils]] in [[Russia]].<ref name=Thermogutta-terrifontis/><ref name=UniProt/><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Parker |first1=Charles Thomas |last2=Garrity |first2=George M |title=Taxonomic Abstract for the species. |journal=The NamesforLife Abstracts |date=1 January 2003 |doi=10.1601/tx.26396 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Details: DSM-26237 |journal=www.dsmz.de |url=https://www.dsmz.de/catalogues/details/culture/DSM-26237.html |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Slobodkina |first1=GB |last2=Kovaleva |first2=OL |last3=Miroshnichenko |first3=ML |last4=Slobodkin |first4=AI |last5=Kolganova |first5=TV |last6=Novikov |first6=AA |last7=van Heerden |first7=E |last8=Bonch-Osmolovskaya |first8=EA |title=Thermogutta terrifontis gen. nov., sp. nov. and Thermogutta hypogea sp. nov., thermophilic anaerobic representatives of the phylum Planctomycetes. |journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology |date=March 2015 |volume=65 |issue=Pt 3 |pages=760–5 |doi=10.1099/ijs.0.000009 |pmid=25479950}}</ref>
